---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy',
  url: 'https://purplepeaksapps.com/privacy',
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Purple Peaks Apps"
  description="How Purple Peaks Apps collects, uses, and protects the information you share with us."
  path="/privacy"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Effective Date: July 15, 2026</p>
      <p class="reviewed">Last reviewed: July 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal">
      <p>
        Purple Peaks Apps LLC ("Purple Peaks Apps," "we," "us," or "our") builds software tools
        for insurance professionals, including the PSG Partner Portal. This Privacy Policy
        explains what information we collect through purplepeaksapps.com (the "Site") and our
        related applications, how we use it, and the choices available to you. By using the Site
        or our applications, you agree to the practices described in this Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you provide directly.</strong> When you submit our contact form,
          we collect your name, email address, and message, and, if you choose to provide it,
          your phone number.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Portal and application data.</strong> If you use the PSG Partner Portal or
          another Purple Peaks Apps product, we collect the account, usage, and content
          information necessary to operate that product, as described in any product-specific
          documentation provided to you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automatically collected information.</strong> We automatically collect
          technical information when you visit the Site, including your IP address, browser
          type, device type, referring URL, pages viewed, and time spent on the Site, through
          cookies and similar technologies described in Section 4.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communications.</strong> If you contact us by phone, email, or through the
          Site, we retain a record of that communication, including any information you
          voluntarily provide.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create and maintain a contact record for you in our customer relationship
          management system (GoHighLevel, "GHL"), so we can respond to your inquiry and follow
          up appropriately;</li>
        <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our software products, including the PSG Partner
          Portal;</li>
        <li>Contact you by phone, text, or email to respond to your inquiry or discuss our
          products and services;</li>
        <li>Monitor and improve the Site's content, usability, security, and performance; and</li>
        <li>Comply with applicable legal, regulatory, and recordkeeping obligations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How Your Contact Form Submission Is Handled</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit the contact form on this Site, your information is transmitted securely
        and used to automatically create or update a contact record in our GoHighLevel CRM. A
        member of our team then reviews your message and reaches out using the contact method(s)
        you provided. A hidden "honeypot" field on the form helps us detect and block automated
        spam submissions; it is not visible to human visitors and no information entered into it
        (there should be none) is used for any purpose other than spam prevention.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies, pixels, and similar technologies to operate the Site, remember your
        preferences, measure traffic and engagement, and support analytics tools. You can control
        cookies through your browser settings; disabling cookies may affect certain Site
        functionality. We do not knowingly sell personal information, as that term is defined
        under applicable state privacy laws.
      </p>

      <h2>5. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers who help us operate the Site and our applications and manage
          contacts, including our CRM provider (GoHighLevel), hosting providers, and email/SMS
          delivery platforms, under confidentiality obligations;</li>
        <li>Business partners only where necessary to provide a product or service you have
          affirmatively requested; and</li>
        <li>Government authorities or regulators, where required by law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Data Retention and Security</h2>
      <p>
        We retain contact and account information for as long as reasonably necessary to fulfill
        the purposes described in this Policy and to comply with applicable legal and
        contractual obligations. We use commercially reasonable administrative and technical
        safeguards to protect your information, but no method of transmission or storage is
        completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the personal information we
        hold about you, or ask us to stop contacting you, by submitting a request through our{' '}
        <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. Depending on your state of residence, you may have
        additional rights under applicable privacy law.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed to individuals under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective Date" above reflects
        the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the updated Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy may be directed to Purple Peaks Apps LLC through our{' '}
        <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-dark) 0%, #2b1147 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .eyebrow { color: var(--color-teal); }
  .subhead { color: #e2d4f0; }
  .reviewed { color: #b6a4cb; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; }
  .legal { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; }
</style>
